{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"59e0dba0-b347-4069-8e1a-149a1f5fafe4","content":"In .NET MAUI, use the **lifecycle events** API in `MauiProgram.cs` (or your app builder setup) via `ConfigureLifecycleEvents`:\n\n```csharp\nusing Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;\n\nbuilder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>\n{\n#if ANDROID\n    events.AddAndroid(android => android\n        .OnPause(activity =>\n        {\n            // Runs when the activity is pausing\n        })\n        .OnStop(activity =>\n        {\n            // Runs when the activity is no longer visible\n        }));\n#endif\n\n#if IOS\n    events.AddiOS(ios => ios\n        .DidEnterBackground(app =>\n        {\n            // Runs when the app enters background\n        }));\n#endif\n});\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- Add `Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents` namespace.\n- Use `#if ANDROID` / `#if IOS` preprocessor directives to keep platform code conditional.\n- The builder methods (`AddAndroid`, `AddiOS`) expose the full set of native lifecycle delegates (e.g., `OnResume`, `WillTerminate`, etc.).\n- This approach avoids needing custom platform projects or partial classes — everything stays in shared code.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"80c2ca90-259a-447e-8c3a-6909b093d9ed","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to hook into platform-specific lifecycle events in .NET MAUI — specifically Android's `OnPause`/`OnStop` and iOS's `DidEnterBackground`. This is a general knowledge question, not a codebase task.","outputTokens":388},"id":"3cd90705-5042-46e0-bb9d-4d4fb61a66b1","timestamp":"2026-04-08T00:44:44.910Z","parentId":"cc739f2c-9819-4ebc-960e-1602a1fc3408"}
